  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>brown</strong> <strong>onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</strong> </span>(as finely as you can!)</p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop the<strong> coriander </strong>roughly (including the stalks)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1656255380697-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1656255380697-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1656255380697-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1656255380697-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1656255380697-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>gram flour</strong> and<strong> curry powder </strong>in a large bowl with a generous pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and 4 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[8 tbsp]</span><strong> cold water</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>sliced onion </strong>to the bowl with the<strong> chopped coriander</strong>, <strong>chopped ginger</strong> and <strong>garlic </strong>and a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and mix until the onion is well coated – this is your<strong> onion bhaji mixture</strong></p><p>Massage the mixture for 30 secs, squeezing the onions to form a thick mixture</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1656255384827-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1656255384827-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1656255384827-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1656255384827-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1656255384827-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Divide the <strong>onion bhaji mixture</strong> into 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span>, then shape into rough patties and add to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray and drizzle with <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min, turning once halfway, or until the bhajis are golden and crispy – these are your <strong>onion bhajis</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
